HEADWORD: Durometer
<hw>Du*rom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>durus</ets> hard + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument for
measuring the degree of hardness; especially, an instrument for testing
the relative hardness of steel rails and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Durous</ent>⟦br⟧
